pecially when you can get your message in front of them for free.\r\n\r\nOptimize Your App Store Rank\r\n\r\nApp Store Optimization (ASO) is the process of making sure your mobile app ranks higher in app store searches. ASO is very similar to Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for websites.\r\n\r\nYour app’s keywords, downloads, ratings, and reviews affect where your app appears in searches. Mobile app development companies use ASO to rank higher in search results and on top of lists in-store, which drives downloads.\r\n\r\nAs 63% of apps are found through app store searches, you need to be sure that your app is seen in the first page of results. Using keywords in your app description and app title will help give it higher visibility in searches. The title of your app should be short, easy to remember, and explain what your app does.\r\n\r\nReviews and ratings allow users to provide direct feedback about your app and can affect ASO.\r\n\r\nAs your rating is placed next to the name of your app, it can immediately reflect positively on your user experience. People will read that others liked your app and believe in the value.\r\n\r\nAlmost all customers (97%) read reviews, which means it is essential to curate good feedback for others to see. If you receive a poor review, make sure to respond and assure them that you will try to fix the problem.\r\n\r\nResponding to user reviews can continue the conversation and further grow the user’s relationship with your brand.\r\n\r\nFine-tuning each aspect of ASO will help increase your total number of downloads.\r\n\r\nPay for Advertisements\r\n\r\nOver 50% of businesses pay for both search and social ads while almost half of clicks (41%) are given to the top 3 paid ads on the search results page. Many companies use both paid social and search ads to maximize their apps’ chances at being seen.\r\n\r\nSearch ads appear as ads at the top of search listings and next to results in the sidebar, while social media ads appear in people’s newsfeed and in the sidebar.\r\n\r\nPaid advertisements have a high success rate because you can target exactly who you are trying to reach.\r\n\r\nSocial media ads target people based on age, location, gender, device, and interest. Meanwhile, search ads appear directly in front of someone searching for a specific service. Both methods allow businesses to appeal directly to their intended audience.\r\n\r\nGoogle also offers metric tracking features when businesses pay for ads. This tracking feature shows how well an ad is performing by telling you how many people have viewed it, the number of clicks, and how many people downloaded your app.\r\n\r\nClosely tracking the success of an ad can help you adapt your marketing for the future.\r\n\r\nBoost Your App Downloads with Great App Marketing Practices\r\n\r\nUsing social media helps you to begin building your relationship with users while ASO ensures potential users can find your app when searching for it.\r\n\r\nPaid advertisements allow your business to either be the first company people see when looking for a service or to notice your product naturally as they look through their own social feeds.\r\n\r\nApp marketing can boost your app’s success and engage potential users. Hire a top mobile app developer or mobile app development company to begin your app development process.','3 Tips to Successfully Market Your App','','inherit','closed','closed','','501-revision-v1','','','2019-03-18 09:19:20','2019-03-18 09:19:20','',501,'http://wow.pebbled.io/schakraborty/softprodigy/1/501-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(506,1,'2019-03-18 09:23:35','2019-03-18 09:23:35','How to stay on top of all the current ICOs?\r\n\r\nSeeing the present situation, when seemingly the new ones appear out of nowhere, and others disappear just as fast.\r\n\r\nAccording to Token Data, ‘2017 had 902 ICOs but by March 2018, 46 percent of these tokens had already failed.’\r\n\r\nIt means that these ICOs were not able to hit their funding goal, a